'''Fangorn''' can refer to:
==Middle-earth==
* [[Treebeard]] the [[Ents|Ent]], also known by the name ''Fangorn''.
* [[Fangorn Forest]], a large forest to the north of [[Rohan]] where [[Treebeard]] and the other Ents live.
==Adaptations==
* ''Fangorn'', the first episode of the second half (and seventh overall) of [[The Lord of the Rings (1955 radio series)]], aired [[19 November|November 19]], [[1956]].
* ''[[Treebeard Of Fangorn]]'', the twelfth episode of [[The Lord of the Rings (1981 radio series)|''The Lord of the Rings'' (1981 radio series)]], aired [[24 May|May 24]], [[1981]].
* ''[[Night Camp at Fangorn]]'', the tenth scene of the [[The Lord of the Rings: The Two Towers (extended edition)|Extended Edition]] of ''[[The Lord of the Rings: The Two Towers]]''.
* ''[[Fangorn Comes to Helm's Deep|Fangorn comes to Helm's Deep]]'', the sixty-first scene of the [[The Lord of the Rings: The Two Towers (extended edition)|Extended Edition]] of ''[[The Lord of the Rings: The Two Towers]]''.
* "[[Fangorn (soundtrack)|Fangorn (song)]]", the tenth track of Disc 1 of ''[[The Lord of the Rings: The Two Towers - The Complete Recordings]]''.

==Fandom==
* "[[Fangorn (Battlelore song)]]", track six on ''[[...Where the Shadows Lie]]'', the first album of [[Battlelore]].
